# Shared Page Components

Don't hand-roll page-level headers, chat split-panes, or toolbar rows. Use the shared primitives listed here so mobile responsiveness is handled consistently.

## Dashboard Page Headers

Use `DashboardPageHeader` from `@/components/dashboard-page-header` for every list/section page in the admin portal. It standardizes the `h1 + description + optional right-side actions` layout and handles mobile (actions drop below the title, primary button grows to fill).

```tsx
import { DashboardPageHeader } from "@/components/dashboard-page-header";

<DashboardPageHeader
  title="Programs"
  description="Manage your registration programs and enrollment options."
  actions={
    <Button asChild>
      <Link href="/dashboard/registrations/programs/new">Add Program</Link>
    </Button>
  }
/>
```

Multiple action buttons — pass as a fragment. Each direct child gets `flex-1` on mobile so the buttons share the row evenly.

```tsx
actions={
  <>
    <Button variant="outline">Secondary</Button>
    <Button>Primary</Button>
  </>
}
```

Sub-pages / create-edit forms — pass `variant="small"` for `text-2xl` titles instead of the default `text-3xl`.

Back button — wrap the back `Button` and `DashboardPageHeader` in a flex row:

```tsx
<div className="flex items-start gap-4">
  <Button variant="ghost" size="icon" asChild className="shrink-0">
    <Link href="/dashboard/events">
      <ArrowLeft className="h-5 w-5" />
    </Link>
  </Button>
  <div className="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <DashboardPageHeader title="Create Event" description="..." />
  </div>
</div>
```

**Never** write `<div className="flex items-center justify-between"><div><h1 className="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">...</h1><p className="text-muted-foreground">...</p></div>...</div>` by hand. It won't be mobile responsive.

## Chat Split-Pane Layout

The three chat pages (admin/coach/athletes) use `ChatPanels` from `@/components/chat/chat-panels` for the sidebar + message-view layout. Compose `ChatPanelsSidebar` and `ChatPanelsMain` as children, and render `ChatPanelsBackButton` inside the main pane's `ChatHeader`. The component swaps to a single-pane layout on mobile driven by the `hasSelection` prop.

```tsx
<ChatPanels
  hasSelection={!!selectedConversationId}
  onBack={() => setSelectedConversationId(null)}
>
  <ChatPanelsSidebar>
    <ConversationSidebar ... />
  </ChatPanelsSidebar>
  <ChatPanelsMain>
    <Chat>
      <ChatHeader>
        <ChatHeaderAddon>
          <ChatPanelsBackButton />
          <ChatHeaderAvatar ... />
        </ChatHeaderAddon>
        ...
      </ChatHeader>
      ...
    </Chat>
  </ChatPanelsMain>
</ChatPanels>
```

## Responsive Toolbars

For the standard "search input + action buttons" row above a table, stack on mobile and switch to the inline layout at `sm:`:

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col gap-2 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
  <div className="relative w-full sm:max-w-sm sm:flex-1">
    <Search className="absolute left-2.5 top-2.5 h-4 w-4 text-muted-foreground" />
    <Input className="pl-8" placeholder="Search..." />
  </div>
  <div className="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
    <Button variant="outline" size="icon" className="shrink-0">
      <Filter className="h-4 w-4" />
    </Button>
    <Button className="flex-1 sm:flex-none">Primary Action</Button>
  </div>
</div>
```

Key classes:
- Search wrapper `w-full sm:max-w-sm sm:flex-1` — full-width on mobile, bounded on desktop
- Buttons group `flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2` — wraps cleanly if cramped
- Primary button `flex-1 sm:flex-none` — grows on mobile, natural width on desktop
- Icon-only utility buttons keep `shrink-0` so they don't get squished

## Data Table Overflow

Wrap any multi-column `<Table>` in `<div className="overflow-x-auto rounded-md border">` so it scrolls horizontally on narrow screens instead of squishing columns.

